Enum DiscoveryServiceAuditCode

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<DiscoveryServiceAuditCode>
      • org.odpi.openmetadata.adapters.connectors.discoveryservices.DiscoveryServiceAuditCode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<DiscoveryServiceAuditCode>
    public enum DiscoveryServiceAuditCode
extends java.lang.Enum<DiscoveryServiceAuditCode>
    The DiscoveryServiceAuditCode is used to define the message content for the OMRS Audit Log. The 5 fields in the enum are:
    • Log Message Id - to uniquely identify the message
    • Severity - is this an event, decision, action, error or exception
    • Log Message Text - includes placeholder to allow additional values to be captured
    • Additional Information - further parameters and data relating to the audit message (optional)
    • SystemAction - describes the result of the situation
    • UserAction - describes how a user should correct the situation
